INSERT INTO `course` (`id`, `title`, `shortDetails`, `details`, `membershipLeval`, `image`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(7,	'CandleStick Course',	'Green candle represents up period in the market and red candle represents down period in the market.  Each candle may have a different length of body and wick depending on open and close of the market.  ',	'<p>Green candle represents up period in the market and red candle represents down period in the market. &nbsp;Each candle may have a different length of body and wick depending on open and close of the market. &nbsp;If a candle has a vertical line at the top and/or bottom of the body of the candle that is called the wick.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://goldenfuturelife.in/tradeGame/assets/uploads/users/secondImage.png\" style=\"height:150px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The body is the highlighted part of the candle that represents the open and close of that candle. &nbsp;The wick on the top of the candle tells you the high price of that candle and the wick on the bottom of the candle tells you the low of that candle. &nbsp;See and study candle pic for visual explanation. &nbsp;Now on the next screen touch the screen to point out high, low, open and close on the candle to make sure you understand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	'3',	'assets/uploads/users/2019-06-29.png',	'2019-06-08 05:48:16',	'2019-06-29 12:29:28'),
(8,	'Charting Course ',	'Support is the zone where alot resting bids (buy orders) are in the market.  Resistance is the zone where alot of resting offers (sell orders) are in the market.  ',	'<h3>Support is the zone where alot resting bids (buy orders) are in the market. &nbsp;Resistance is the zone where alot of resting offers (sell orders) are in the market. &nbsp;When price hits support or resistance there is a higher probability the price will get thrown in opposite direction. &nbsp;When price goes below or breaks through support to the downside it turns into resistance making it harder to break back above that level. &nbsp;When price goes above resistance it turns into support making it difficult to break back below that level. &nbsp;Bids is the price that the buyer is willing to pay. &nbsp;Offers is the price that sellers are willing to pay. See pic 1c and 1d for visual explanation. &nbsp;Over the next few slides you will get blank charts and I want you to take you finger and draw support and resistance lines horizontally.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://goldenfuturelife.in/tradeGame/assets/uploads/users/firstImage.png\" style=\"height:150px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Now that you are familiar with horizontal support and resistance lines let&rsquo;s talk about diagonal support and resistance lines otherwise known as channels. &nbsp;When a stock is hitting a support line but continue to make a higher low and higher high that is known as an upward channel better known as a trend. &nbsp;Conversely when a stock makes lower low and lower high that is known as a down trend or channel. See pic 1e and 1f for visual explanation. &nbsp;Over the next few slides you will get blank charts and I want you to take you finger and draw channel for up trend and down trend.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</h3>\r\n',	'3',	'assets/uploads/users/2019-06-29_(1).png',	'2019-06-08 06:06:31',	'2019-06-29 12:29:20'),
(14,	'Trend Following Course',	'There are many different strategies to employ when trading short term.  In this course we will look at a few strategies that are the most profitable for us at Relentless Trade. ',	'<p>There are many different strategies to employ when trading short term.&nbsp; In this course we will look at a few strategies that are the most profitable for us at Relentless Trade.&nbsp; These strategies will be for traders and investors that are working 9 to 5 jobs and or busy doing the day where the market cant be watched all day and everyday. One of the simplest strategies is known as Swing Trading.&nbsp; Swing Trading is identifying an uptrend (higher highs and higher lows) and buying if the stock trades higher than the pullback&rsquo;s previous day&rsquo;s high.&nbsp; So when you see the stock move higher then the previous swing high you would generally buy the stock and hold as long as it doesn&#39;t trade below the previous swing low or exit on a predetermined resistance level.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	'3',	'assets/uploads/users/Downtrend_Swing_Trade.PNG',	'2019-07-27 13:22:02',	'2019-07-27 13:22:02'),
(19,	'Day Trading Course',	'Day Trading Course.  Day Trading is one of the hardest ways to make money in the stock market.  To Day Trade means you are buying and selling all in the same day never carrying a position overnight.  Learning to successful day trade takes a lot of practice.  There are may different strategies that you can employ trading intra day but we will talk about some of the most successful strategies we use that includes learning about level II, time and sales which few professionals talk about. ',	'<p>Day Trading Course.&nbsp; Day Trading is one of the hardest ways to make money in the stock market.&nbsp; To Day Trade means you are buying and selling all in the same day never carrying a position overnight.&nbsp; Learning to successful day trade takes a lot of practice.&nbsp; There are may different strategies that you can employ trading intra day but we will talk about some of the most successful strategies we use that includes learning about level II, time and sales which few professionals talk about.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	'3',	'assets/uploads/users/1140639321177234_5pi73gZKCgTUgfv6lzeY_height640.png',	'2019-09-19 13:49:33',	'2019-09-19 13:49:33'),
(18,	'Trading Psychology Course.',	'The market reflects the actions of its participants and those actions are influenced by what everyone is thinking. As you engage the markets, you will discover things about yourself that may be surprising.',	'<p>Trading Psychology Course.&nbsp; The market reflects the actions of its participants and those actions are influenced by what everyone is thinking. As you engage the markets, you will discover things about yourself that may be surprising.&nbsp; One of the main keys of successful trading is identifying those tendencies, attitudes, and behaviors undermining your trading objectives. There is usually a gap between how we actually do things and how we think we do them. In order to make any changes, you need to measure this gap and then derive a plan to close it. This process begins with a realistic assessment of where your trading is right now.The least talked about thing in trading is the most important thing in trading and that is Psychology.&nbsp; Even though you may know when you want to enter and when you want to exit doing it under pressure is very difficult.&nbsp; The reason why there so much pressure is because you have to make split decisions, constantly with real money involved.&nbsp; The holy grail or most important skill a trader can possess is trading without emotion.&nbsp; In trading and life, some things work and others don&#39;t. Trading psychology is about taking inventory of both and making adjustments to improve not only your performance, but also to enhance your experience along the way. The primary objective of trading psychology is to help you stick to your plan. It is hard to reach your destination without it. It is said that &lsquo;luck is when opportunity meets preparation&rsquo;. Trading psychology helps the mind prepare to meet both the market&rsquo;s opportunities and its risks.&nbsp; At Relentless trade we focus more on psychology than we do strategy because knowing what to do is one thing and having the discipline to do it is totally different.</p>\r\n',	'3',	'assets/uploads/users/1137084142477951_9HrMmZFvbl3V9m4O4qYP_height640.png',	'2019-09-07 12:25:10',	'2019-09-07 12:25:10'),
(17,	'Stock Option Course',	'A stock option gives a trader and/or investor the right',	'<p>A stock option gives a trader and/or investor the right, but not the obligation, to buy or sell a stock at an agreed upon price and date. There are two types of options: puts, which is a bet that a stock will go down, or calls, which is a bet that a stock will go up. &nbsp;The image above is an option chain. &nbsp;An option chain tells you what is available for each stock if that stock is optionable. &nbsp;If you look at the dates on the left it tells you all the different expiration periods. &nbsp;Stock have either weekly, monthly, quarterly or all the above contracts. &nbsp;In this course we will talk extensively about the important stuff that you need to trade stock options successfully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://carz91.com/tradeGame/assets/uploads/users/Option_Chain.PNG\" style=\"height:311px; width:991px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This an image of an opened option chain.&nbsp; When you open the option chain you get a lot of valuable information that you need to make decisions according to your trading system and plan.&nbsp; An option chain gives you volume, open interest, the bid/ask spread, and greeks for both calls and puts.&nbsp; Greeks are delta, gamma, theta and vega which we will talk more about as we go through the course.&nbsp; Depending on your brokerage you can customize your option chain to fit your needs and what information you need to make trading decisions.&nbsp; Generally you want to trade options that have some volume and open interest. The more traders in a particular options strike, the better the chances you&rsquo;ll have to get in and out of your trade without too much slippage.&nbsp; There are many different factors that go into option pricing and how it changes over time according to how the security moves.&nbsp; Delta tells you how much the option will move for every point the security moves.&nbsp; For example if the security move up one point the option would appreciate $0.48 on the 128 calls strike price.&nbsp; Gamma tells you how much the delta will change for every one point move of the security.&nbsp; For example when looking at the 128 calls if the security moves up one point gamma will change delta from $0.48 to $0.57.&nbsp; Theta is time decay so for everyday that passes the option will depreciate whatever amount theta states.&nbsp; All options depreciate regardless if it moves or not.&nbsp; The closer the option gets to expiration date the more it decays or depreciates.&nbsp; That&#39;s why the further out in time you purchase the option the more expensive it will be.&nbsp; For example when looking at the 128 calls everyday that passes the option will depreciate -$0.08.&nbsp; Vega tells us how much an option will change for every percentage move in implied volatility.&nbsp; For example if implied volatility goes up by one percent the 128 calls will increase $0.08.&nbsp; Learning to trade options takes time and practice.&nbsp; There are many different option strategies including spreads and straddles that we will go over.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://carz91.com/tradeGame/assets/uploads/users/190_Credit_Spread.PNG\" style=\"height:403px; width:432px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many different option strategies to trade depending on what your analysis of the market is.&nbsp; We will go over the essential spreads and strategies to be profitable.&nbsp; We will discuss buying and selling single calls and puts toward the end of the course because it is the simplest and easiest to understand.&nbsp; The first option strategy we will discuss is the vertical spread.&nbsp; There are 2 types of vertical spreads credit spreads and debit spreads. Credit Spreads is selling one option strike price while buying another option strike price.&nbsp; If you&#39;re buying a call you need to be selling a call.&nbsp; If you&#39;re buying a put you should be selling a put to be a credit spread.&nbsp; You&#39;re not buying a call option strike and selling a put option strike.&nbsp; For example if you look at the image of the put option chain you can sell the 190 strike price and buy the 185 strike price.&nbsp; When you do that you will bring in a credit into your account.&nbsp; So if you get filled on the buy order of $2.50 and the sell order of $3.25 you will bring in $0.75 into your account.&nbsp; You generally want to place your orders halfway between the bid and ask price to get the best prices.&nbsp; As long as that stock don&#39;t close below 190 on expiration, which for this option is the third Friday of the month, you will keep the full amount you initially made of $0.75.&nbsp; If it starts to trade below the 190 price you want to close out the trade by buying back the 190 strike you initially sold and selling the 185 you initially bought.&nbsp; To trade a put credit spread you always have to sell the higher strike price and buy the lower strike price,&nbsp; To trade a call credit spread you always have to buy the higher strike price and sell the lower strike price.&nbsp; Lots of Practice!</p>\r\n',	'6',	'assets/uploads/users/1135132251738024_pqX7Pc2Gp1mVnfhvx6tB_height64012.png',	'2019-08-17 12:49:04',	'2019-08-17 12:49:04'),
